Eser proposes to equate extremism with insulting patriotic feelings
In order to legally protect the patriotic feelings of citizens from provocations and insults directed against Russia, Just Russia proposes to equate the insulting of patriotic feelings with extremist activity and punish it with five years in prison.
According to the newspaper “Izvestia”, such amendments to the legislation, prepared by the Deputy Chairman of the Duma Committee on energy Oleg Mikheev, have already been sent to obtain an opinion in the Supreme court and the government.
By patriotic feelings of citizens, the author of the amendments proposes to understand the emotional connection of a person with a country of which he is a citizen, characterized by a love for this country, a responsible attitude to its fate, respect for its history and culture.
As Mikheev points out, in domestic legislation there are sanctions for abuse of formal signs of state power - the flag and the coat of arms.
At the same time, according to the MP, the protection of Russians, whose feelings can be hurt by insulting state symbols, and other manifestations of disrespect for our country, is not sufficiently worked out in Russian legislation.
As an example, he cites the discussions unfolding annually on the eve of Victory Day, when some media personalities allow themselves to question the heroic feat of the people of the USSR in the fight against the fascists.
On the eve of the main national holiday - Victory Day on May 9 - a real bacchanalia unfolds annually.
Exercising in wit and an "alternative view" of history, some publicists come to the conclusion that, they say, it is a pity that the cultural Germans did not conquer the wild Soviet Union!
I consider this absolutely unacceptable in a country where pride in history remains the main "spiritual bond" of the nation," Oleg Mikheev is outraged.
In addition, according to Mikheev, patriotic people in Russia are much more than religious, but the law punishes for insulting the feelings of believers, and you can insult patriotic feelings with almost impunity.
According to him, it is necessary to equate the insult of patriotic feelings to extremist activity and to prescribe the corresponding punishment in Article 282 of the Criminal Code.
The bill provides for punishment for insulting patriotic feelings: from a 100,000th fine to a five-year sentence.
