Recall that three years ago on December 11, a spontaneous rally of nationalists took place on Manezhnaya Square, which turned into mass riots.
“Levada-center” also asked the Russians about what holiday is celebrated on November 4.
Over the past two years, the number of those who know the correct answer (National Unity Day) has increased from 41% to 49%.
