Due to the new rules introduced by Russian customs, hundreds of trucks have queued on the border with Russia for almost a week.
Donetsk officials have promised to provide drivers with drinking water and install toilets
At the border points at the entrance to Russia accumulated hundreds of trucks.
This situation arose due to a change in the rules of customs clearance of goods.
Ukrainian border guards and customs officers confirm that the queue is created by the Russian side, which did not warn about the innovations in advance.
From October 28, the customs authorities of Russia began to apply additional measures to guarantee the delivery of goods, - said Deputy head of Eastern customs Vladimir Denisov.
The new model document is applied in countries that have acceded to the convention on international transportation.
The checkpoints are working in an enhanced mode.
The correspondent of "FACTS" visited the border and talked with truckers who were hostages of the situation.
Prices in the roadside shop-cafe at the checkpoint "Novoazovsk" are growing every day, as well as the queue of trucks.
Trucks stand in several rows, stretching for about two kilometers.
The Novoazovsk-Voznesenka customs terminal provides one of the most important transport destinations from the south of Ukraine along the international highway.
From here, cargoes are sent to the Stavropol Territory of Russia, Kazakhstan, Georgia, Armenia.
On Sunday, before midnight, they were still allowed, and after they introduced these rules, - complains truck driver Alexei Golovanov (pictured), who is carrying cargo from Turkey to Kazakhstan in transit through Russia and has been sleeping in his car for almost a week.
According to the new rules, in order to cross the border, I need an additional package of documents and payment for cargo insurance.
The amount depends on the cost of the cargo and the distance to which it is transported.
The minimum insurance is 4.5-5 thousand rubles (about 1100-1300 hryvnia).
Those who travel nearby (say, to Georgia, Armenia) with cargo worth up to 50 thousand dollars, pay somewhere 15 thousand rubles (3800 hryvnia) and pass.
And the rest are stuck - because no one has such a lot of money with him!
Imagine, if the driver is carrying a cargo worth only four thousand dollars, but all the way to Moscow, he needs 90 thousand rubles (almost 23 thousand hryvnia) to pay for transit!
Conditions for survival at the border - no, - complain truckers, arranged to eat near their cars.
In the border shops and cafes are always expensive, but such prices as here, we have not met anywhere!
The sellers orientated and quickly inflated them: 15 hryvnia is a baton, seven hryvnia is a cup of coffee, 25 hryvnia is a plate of soup.
The cafe is alone.
And there's no toilet.
We sleep in the steppe, we go to the toilet there.
No washing, no shaving...
I can stay out of the car for a week, my wife has prepared everything for me on the road.
A week will last, - comforts another truck driver Viktor Skotarenko.
Will I get to my car in a week?
How much do you have one and a half liters of water? - we are interested in the only border store.
There are 11 and 15 hryvnias.
What, a crystal bottle or water insisted on silver?
We have a cafe, not a store.
Take while there is something else, - the seller parries.
After the situation began to be covered in the media, the plight of Ukrainian drivers drew the attention of the regional authorities.
The leadership of the Amvrosiivka and Novoazovskaya district state administrations were instructed to provide all those who stand in line on the Ukrainian-Russian border with drinking water, said Acting Chairman of the Donetsk Regional State Administration Sergey Dergunov.
Ambulance crews are now on duty at the checkpoints.
Bio-toilets will also be installed for the convenience of people.
According to the official, the problem associated with the queues will be resolved in the coming days.
