Pensions increase in Belarus since November
Pensions have been increasing in Belarus since November, BelTA learned from the main pension department of the Ministry of Labor and Social Protection.
From November 1 of this year, the average wage of employees in the republic, applied during the previous recalculation of pensions, will be adjusted with a 5.4% increase in its value and the corresponding recalculation of labor pensions will be made in accordance with the decree of October 21, 2013 No. 478 "On increasing pensions".
As a result of the recalculation from November, labor pensions for age will increase, according to estimates, by an average of 5.3%.
The average old-age pension will be Br2 million 295,000.
The increase in pensions will affect 2.4 million residents of the republic.
Expenditures of the Social Protection Fund of the Ministry of Labor and Social Protection of Belarus for the payment of pensions in increased amounts from November of this year will increase by Br274.3 billion per month.
Simultaneously with the recalculation of labor pensions in November of this year, minimum and social pensions, allowances, increases and additional payments to pensions will be recalculated in connection with the increase in the budget of the subsistence minimum on average per capita.
BPM for the period from November 1, 2013 to January 31, 2014 was approved by the government in the amount of Br1 million 47 thousand 530 - 2.1% higher than the one in effect from August 1 to October 31.
Accordingly, by 2.1% from November 1, the size of minimum labor pensions, social pensions and allowances, increases and additional payments to pensions will be increased.
In Belarus, more than Br53 trillion was pledged for the payment of pensions taking into account increases in 2013.
